definitions.definition: The back side of a flat object which is to be examined visually, as for reading, such as a sheet, leaf, coin or medal ;

subdefinitions.definition: The left-hand page of a book of a script which reads from left to right, usually having an even page number.

main_definition: The back side of a flat object which is to be examined visually, as for reading, such as a sheet, leaf, coin or medal ;
